ily, reaching as far as Gela and Agrigento. The ground floor covers prehistory through to the end of the Classical period. Upstairs includes Hellenistic and Roman Syracuse and a display of material from the catacombs. A gallery displaying material from Hellenistic eastern Sicily is in preparation.",{"settlement":86,"region":86,"country":124,"address":125,"geo":126},"Italy","Viale Teocrito 66, 96100 - Siracusa",{"lat":127,"lon":128},37.07636989,15.2866213,{"_":130,"mainLang":131,"languages":132},"Ancient Greek","grc",[130],{"type":134,"bibl":135},"edition",[136,148],{"type":137,"n":138,"citedRange":139,"ptr":140,"ref":141,"title":142,"author":143,"date":144,"citation":145,"uri":146,"year":147},"bulletin","SEG","49.1331.6",{"target":141},"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/F2GG87EQ","Supplementum epigraphicum graecum","","1923-","\u003Cspan>‘Supplementum Epigraphicum Graecum’, \u003Ci>Supplementum Epigraphicum Graecum\u003C/i>, 1923, \u003Ca href=\"http://www.worldcat.org/oclc/1607583\">http://www.worldcat.org/oclc/1607583\u003C/a>\u003C/span>","https://www.zotero.org/groups/isicily/items/F2GG87EQ","1923",{"author":149,"date":150,"citedRange":151,"ptr":152,"ref":153,"inscriptionDate":150,"title":154,"citation":155,"uri":156,"year":150},"Manganaro","1999","68 no.62 fig.144",{"target":153},"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/GRB3IPD5","Sikelika: studi di antichità e di epigrafia della Sicilia greca","\u003Cspan>Giacomo Manganaro, \u003Ci>Sikelika: studi di antichità e di epigrafia della Sicilia greca\u003C/i>, Biblioteca di QUCC 8 (Pisa, Roma: Istituti Editoriali e Poligrafici internazionali, 1999)\u003C/span>","https://www.zotero.org/groups/isicily/items/GRB3IPD5",{"type":158,"bibl":159},"discussion",[19],{"editor":161,"principal":163,"contributors":164,"change":184},{"_":162,"ref":102},"Jonathan Prag",{"_":162,"ref":102},[165,168,172,176,180],{"_":162,"xml:id":166,"ref":167},"JP","http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537",{"_":169,"xml:id":170,"ref":171},"