 Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2018-03-15\" src=\"ISic003500_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic003500.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2018-03-15\" src=\"ISic003500-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic003500_rear_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2018-03-15\" src=\"ISic003500_rear_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic003500_rear.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2018-03-15\" src=\"ISic003500_rear-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text from autopsy\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"1\">1: \u003Cspan>Γ also possible\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"3\">3: \u003Cspan>Manganaro: ΑΙ[--]; the vertical is visible, but whether it is isolated is impossible to say.\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"4\">4: \u003Cspan>Omitted by Manganaro; second letter could be Μ or Ν\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"6\">6: \u003Cspan>Manganaro: ΠΙ[--]; if not Ρ then Γ\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2> translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">  \u003C/p>\u003Cp>  \u003C/p>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>Included by Manganaro in a list of fragments suggested to be lists of names, whether ephebes or others, but it is impossible to speculate on the content on the basis of initial letters alone. The size of the letters distinguishes it from other Hellenistic lists of names, where they are generally smaller. The piece has not so far been identified in the inventory, and origin is unknown (but presumably Syracusan). \u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> 49.1331.6 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Manganaro 1999 68 no.62 fig.144 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001813\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001813\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"handnote\">\u003Cp>Simple letters without serifs. Broken bar alpha; Mu with vertical outer strokes, short inner strokes.\u003C/p> Line 1-6  30-34  Interlineation line 1 to 6  10-15  \u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. \u003C/div>",[216,219,222,225,228,231,234,237],{"id":217,"html":218},"editions","\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Valentina Mignosa, Jonathan Prag; edition source: autopsy Prag, 2018-03-15, Magazzino B, MARPO\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>Π̣[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>Μ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>Α\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">.\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al4-interpretive\">\u0