s, whether ephebes or others, but it is impossible to speculate on the content on the basis of initial letters alone. The size of the letters distinguishes it from other Hellenistic lists of names, where they are generally smaller. The piece has not so far been identified in the inventory, and origin is unknown (but presumably Syracusan). \u003C/p>  ",{"id":232,"html":233},"bibliography","\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> 49.1331.6 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Manganaro 1999 68 no.62 fig.144 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001813\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001813\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  ",{"id":235,"html":236},"handnote","\u003Cp>Simple letters without serifs. Broken bar alpha; Mu with vertical outer strokes, short inner strokes.\u003C/p> Line 1-6  30-34  Interlineation line 1 to 6  10-15  ",{"id":238,"html":239},"license"," Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. ",[241,243,246,247],{"html":242},"Text encoding: Valentina Mignosa, Jonathan Prag; edition source: autopsy Prag, 2018-03-15, Magazzino B, MARPO",{"id":244,"lang":131,"html":245},"edition-interpretive","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>Π̣[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>Μ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>Α\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">.\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al4-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>Α\u003Cspan di