                     \u003Csupport>\u003Cp>Fragment of the local limestone, intact on the left margin, possibly intact above, but broekn to the right and below. The rear is cut roughtly straight. could be part of a plaque or stele.\u003C/p>\n                                    \u003Cmaterial ana=\"#material.stone.limestone\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/66.html\">limestone\u003C/material>\n                                    \u003CobjectType ana=\"#object.unknown\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/2.html\">unknown\u003C/objectType>\n                                    \u003Cdimensions>\n                                        \u003Cheight unit=\"cm\">29\u003C/height>\n                                        \u003Cwidth unit=\"cm\">10\u003C/width>\n                                        \u003Cdepth unit=\"cm\">6\u003C/depth>\n                                    \u003C/dimensions>\n                                \u003C/support>\n                                \u003Ccondition ana=\"#condition.fragment\"/>\n\t\t    \u003C/supportDesc>\n                            \u003ClayoutDesc>\n                                \u003Clayout>\u003Cp>Initial letters of six lines, preserving a consistent left margin, c.2 letter spaces in from the edge, but not quite perpendicular to the margin.\u003C/p>\n                                    \u003Crs ana=\"#execution.chiselled\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1\">chiselled\u003C/rs>\n                                \t\u003Cdamage ana=\"#text_condition.incomplete\"/>\n\t\t\t\u003C/layout>\n                            \u003C/layoutDesc>\n                        \u003C/objectDesc>\n                        \u003ChandDesc>\n                            \u003ChandNote>\u003Cp>Simple letters without serifs. Broken bar alpha; Mu with vertical outer strokes, short inner strokes.\u003C/p>\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line1\" to=\"line6\">Line 1-6\u003C/locus>\n        